# mc-texture-viewer — Project context

This project is **mc-texture-viewer**: a web-embeddable 3D viewer for Minecraft-style models (glTF/GLB and OBJ+MTL). It is a single Web Component with no backend.

## Naming and surface

- **Package / repo name:** `mc-texture-viewer`
- **Custom element tag:** `<mc-texture-viewer>`
- **Global (IIFE bundle):** `window.McTextureViewer` (e.g. `McTextureViewer.warpedForestManifest`)
- **Output bundle:** `dist/mc-texture-viewer.js`

When editing code, docs, or config, use these names. Do not use the old name `mc-viewer-embed`.

## Structure

- **`src/embed.ts`** — Entry point; only registers the custom element and exposes `window.McTextureViewer` for demo manifests.
- **`src/viewer/`** — Core logic: `McViewerElement.ts` (Web Component), `SceneManager.ts` (Three.js scene, loaders, textures), `textureManifest.ts`, `types.ts`.
- **`index.html`** — Single demo page; loads sources via Vite, toolbar with model selector, ZIP upload, rotation and light controls.
- **`models/`** — 3D models; one subfolder per model (OBJ+MTL or GLB).
- **`assets/`** — Default texture pack in **Minecraft resource pack** layout (paths start at `assets/`, e.g. `assets/minecraft/textures/block/`). Set `texture-base-url` to `./assets/` (or equivalent).

## Conventions

- Attributes: `model-url`, `texture-base-url`, `auto-rotate`, `sun-enabled`. Use kebab-case in HTML and reflected camelCase in JS.
- Public API: `setTextureManifest()`, `applyTextureZip(blob)`. Events: `model-loaded`, `mc-texture-viewer-error` (failures; not named `error` — avoids SES/browser `ErrorEvent` clashes), `texture-pack-applied`. `window.McTextureViewer.ERROR_EVENT` matches the error event name.
- Texture manifest maps material/slot names to texture filenames; default pack from `texture-base-url`, overrides from ZIP with fallback to default.

## Directory name

If the repo root folder is still named something else (e.g. `tmpName`), it can be renamed to **mc-texture-viewer** for consistency. The package name and all references in code are already `mc-texture-viewer`.
